@node Introduction "Introduction to Index View"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

  Index  View is a small utility, which allows to view INDEX file of Aminet
just  like  amigaguide  documents.   All  required  conversions are done in
realtime, so you needn't make any conversions.

  Main features of Index View:
    - You  needn't  convert  INDEX file,  which you downloaded from Aminet.
      It's still easy readable text file.
    - INDEX file has more than 4MB of data, but Index View should work even
      on Amigas with only 512KB of free memory.
    - Utility called Integrate allows to add files listed in RECENT file to
      INDEX.   You  needn't  download  4MB of data if you want to have full
      list of Aminet files, just download RECENT once a week.
    - Viewing  an AmigaGuide document is much more comfortable than viewing
      just simple text file.
    - It's very cheap, since it's freeware.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Index View Requirements"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

  Index  View  should run on any Amiga with Kickstart 2.0+.  It should work
even  with  512KB  of memory.  But since I own a better machine I can't say
for sure.  I have tested my program on an A1200/Kickstart 3.0/6MB of RAM
with MC68020 and MC68040 processor.

  Of  course you also need INDEX and TREE, two files downloaded from one of
many  Aminet  sites.   I  downloaded  these files from ftp.doc.ic.ac.uk and
ftp.wustl.edu.   You  can  also use "long" version of INDEX from info/index
directory.

  I  think that hard disk is required, since an INDEX file has over 4MB and
it can't be stored on a floppy disk.
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

  First  you  must  create a new drawer and copy Index View (with its icon)
there. Do the same with @{"Integrate" LINK Integrate} and @{"Fix Index" LINK FixIndex} utilities if you want to
use  them.   Now  copy  to  this  directory  INDEX file and TREE file, both
downloaded from your favourite Aminet site.  If the INDEX file doesn't have
an  "age"  column,  add the "NOAGE" tooltype to IndexView's and Integrate's
icons.
@endnode

@node Usage "How to use Index View"

  @{b}@{u}Usage@{uu}@{ub}

  If  everything  is  installed properly, you should be able to start Index
View  (double click on its icon on Workbench).  Now Index View should start
scaning  INDEX  file,  it  can  take  about one minute.  Don't worry.  Scan
report  is  saved  in INDEX.scan file, so the next time you run Index View,
you  won't  have  to  wait.   If everything is fine, you'll see an index of
Aminet  as  an  AmigaGuide document.  Select directories, which you want to
view, and enjoy using Index View!

  Index View buffers I/O operations to increase the speed.  You can set the
size  of the buffer using "BUFFER" tooltype.  For example "BUFFER=32" means
that  you  want  32KB  buffer.   Buffer  size  must  be between 5 and 1024.
Default is 128.

  If your INDEX file doesn't have an "age" column, add the "NOAGE" tooltype
to program's icon.
@endnode

@node Integrate "About Integrate utility"

  @{b}@{u}Integrate@{uu}@{ub}

  Every  day  dozens  of  new files appear on Aminet INDEX.  So you have to
download  RECENT  file, which contains the list of the latest uploads.  But
every  week  means another file, so after few weeks, you have many RECENTs.
It's highly uncomfortable.  If you ever wondered how to add files listed in
RECENT to INDEX, Integrate is the solution of your problems.

  Save  the  RECENT file in the drawer where INDEX and Integrate are in and
double  click on Integrate icon.  After about one minute your INDEX will be
updated.   Old  version  of  INDEX  will  be renamed to INDEX.old.  You can
delete it, since it's unnecessary.

  Integrate  buffers I/O operations to increase the speed.  You can set the
size  of the buffer using "BUFFER" tooltype.  For example "BUFFER=32" means
that  you  want  32KB  buffer.   Buffer  size  must  be between 5 and 1024.
Default is 128.

  If your INDEX file doesn't have an "age" column, add the "NOAGE" tooltype
to  Integrate's  icon.   Otherwise  an age of all files from the INDEX file
will  be  increased  and  files  from RECENT will have the age value set to
zero.
@endnode

@node FixIndex "About Fix Index utility"

  @{b}@{u}Fix Index@{uu}@{ub}

  Index  View  works  with  original  INDEX  files from Aminet, but you may
remove  an  "age" column if you want.  It may be useful when you get a list
of new uploads daily (not weekly), so when you use Integrate utility an age
column it can't be increased correctly.

  Save  the  INDEX file in the drawer where FixIndex is in and double click
on  FixIndex icon.  After about one minute your INDEX will be updated.  Old
version  of  INDEX  will be renamed to INDEX.old.  You can delete it, since
it's unnecessary.

  Integrate  buffers I/O operations to increase the speed.  You can set the
size  of the buffer using "BUFFER" tooltype.  For example "BUFFER=32" means
that  you  want  32KB  buffer.   Buffer  size  must  be between 5 and 1024.
Default is 128.
@endnode

